By @grillhunters 
.
Have you ever had a grilled romaine salad before? If not, you’re in for a unique and delicious smoky surprise.

Here’s a list of ingredients for the marinade and salad. Full recipe with instruction is on the blog.

// Garlic & herbs marinade //
- 3/4 cup olive oil
- 1 lemon juice
- 1 tbsp basil, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp chives, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp rosemary, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp parsley, fresh & finely chopped
- 1 tbsp lemon zest
- 3 garlic cloves, minced
- 1/2 tsp chili powder
- 1 tsp salt
- 1 tsp black pepper

// Grilles Romaine Salad //
- 1 heart romaine lettuce cut in half lengthwise 
- ½ cup Parmesan cheese flakes
- 4 slice bacon grilled and crispy
- 4 tbsp olive oil extra virgin
- 1 tbsp kosher salt
- 1 lemon juice
- 1 tsp back pepper
- ½ lemon zest

👩🏻‍🍳🥞🍴Soo many yummy Pancakes 🥞 Breakfast options! What are you going for?…1,2,3,4,5 or 6?
...
📸 + Below deets by @healthymoodsf ❤️

1️⃣ CEREAL PANCAKES! These are just small pancakes made into a cereal with berries

2️⃣Rice cake partyyyyyy…Toppings include mashed avocado + olive oil+ sea salt flakes
peanut butter with bananas + hemp seeds + chia seeds + honey 
Peanut butter + strawberries + chia seeds
PB + Jelly + Cream cheese + cucumber + “everything but the bagel” seasoning

3️⃣Curried scrambled eggs, cinnamon raisin PB & jelly toast, 🍓, avocado toast drizzled with EVOO and sprinkled with pink salt flakes

4️⃣COCONUT BANANA PANCAKES 🥥🍌
1 banana + 1 egg + 3 tbsp of coconut flour + 1/2 tsp of baking powder + 1/2 tsp cinnamon✨
mash the banana, add whisked egg, baking powder, coconut flour and cinnamon. mix well and form pancakes into 4-5 inch cakes and cook in a pan coated with coconut oil at low heat with lid for 3-4 minutes on each side. drizzle with some maple butter and enjoy!

5️⃣Sunday Paleo Pancake Stacks😍👏🏻
Paleo mix and added 1 egg, 1/4 c flax meal and 1 mashed banana to the batter and cooked in a pan on low heat with the lid on until ready. 
we paired them with plain yogurt, creamy PB and maple syrup.

6️⃣GF LEMON RICOTTA PANCAKES 🍋🍋🍋 😍🙌🏻
8 oz (1 cup) ricotta cheese + 2 tsp coconut sugar + 1 tsp lemon juice + lemon zest from 1 lemon + 1/2 tsp vanilla extract + 1 egg + 4 tbsp almond flour + 2 tbsp brown rice flour…Directions: combine all ingredients.
heat a skillet over medium heat and add coconut oil. form cakes into balls with lightly floured hands, and put them into the skillet, press and lower the heat. cook for about 3-4 minutes on each side uncovered. once ready, cover with the lid and let it cook for another 1-2 minutes.

Epic Breakfast Quesadilla! Perfect for when you have leftover tortillas!🔥 by @cookingwithayeh

I’m telling you, breakfast will never be the same again! 😋😋😋

Fillings:
Smashed avocado topped with bagel seasoning
1 scrambled egg
Cheese
Tomato
Topped with BBQ on the egg

Start my scrambling your egg.
Then make a cut 1/2 way down a tortilla or wrap, add your fillings to each quarter of the wrap.
Starting at the side where you have made your cut, fold each quarter in like a cute little pocket & then pop into a sandwich press until you get that cheesy goodness!

Tips is to let the egg cool down slightly before adding it to the tortilla. Also don’t overfill each quarter as it will be harder to fold over.

Enjoy lovelies! 

Music by LiQWYD

OLD ME vs. NEW ME 💛🌱 ⁠
⁠Some more great hacks and tips for the kitchen, not only saving energy, resources, time and promoting good health, but also making a difference to our environment! 🌏 

⁠
Pictures and tips from @reducewastenow. ⁠Some notes on each below:⁠⁠
⁠
1 - After cutting your avocado, leave the pit in whenever possible and splash the avocado flesh with lemon juice. Next, store sliced avocado in a reusable container with the lid sealed on. 🥑⁠
⁠
2 - Blend greens for an easy way to sneak in veggies in your smoothies.⁠
⁠
3 - If your red onions are about to go bad, pickle them!⁠
⁠
4 - Revive kale leaves by place them in water in the fridge.⁠
⁠
5 - Raw ginger keeps for about 1 week at room temperature, and 1 month in the fridge… but keeps for up to 6 MONTHS in the freezer! If you freeze ginger pre-chopped in an ice cube tray, let it freeze overnight then pop the ginger out and place the ginger cubes in a reusable container in the freeze⁠
⁠
6 - Another hack for reusing lemon peels!⁠
⁠

node.text:
Follow 👉 @bodysmartfitness for the best nutrition, mindset and fitness tips
.
What bowl 🥣 is your go to!?? 1️⃣↔️6️⃣ comment below and let me know!👇 
All these by @daliciousdish 
-
1️⃣BURGER BOWL🍔 
.
.
Loaded burger bowls! A bowl of all the goods!
.
.
80/20 ground Chuck 
Colbey Jack cheese 
Bread & butter pickles 
sweet potato fries 
Avocado 
Grape tomatoes 
Red onions 
.
. 
#dEATS Burger patties seasoned with sea salt and pepper. Air-fry the sweet potato fries at 400 degrees for 15 mins.Hope everyone is having a wonderful day!

2️⃣ Shrimp bowl 🦐 
.
.
A bowl of all the goods! I had some lettuce I needed to use and decided to make a loaded salad bowl!
.
.
Pan seared jumbo shrimp
Black beans 
Grape tomatoes
Corn
double roasted salsa for dressing
.
. 
#dEATS Shrimp seasoned with garlic powder, smoked paprika, sea salt and pepper. On medium heat, sear each side for 2-3 mins with avocado oil. 
.
3️⃣turmeric falafel 
Campari tomatoes
Cucumbers
Feta cheese
Kalamata olives 
.
.
4️⃣Chicken Cobb🥗 
.
.
Nothing like a classic salad for dinner tonight! 
.
.
Grilled chicken breast 
Spring mix
Grape tomatoes
Avocado 
Red onions 
Blue cheese crumbles 
boiled eggs
.
.
#dEATS Grilled chicken breast seasoned with garlic powder, smoked paprika, S&P. You can bake at 375 for 42-45 mins. For dressing, I used regular balsamic vinegar!

5️⃣Blue Cheese Steak
.
.
We all know that avocado & toast pairs perfect, but man does steak & blue cheese pairs perfectly, too 😍
.
.
6oz filet
Spring mix
Campari tomatoes
Red onions
Avocado
Blue cheese 
Balsamic vinegar for dressing 
.
.
#dEATS Grilled 6oz filet seasoned with lemon pepper, sea salt, & fresh cracked pepper! 

6️⃣SALSA VERDE CHICKEN BOWL 
.
.
It’s definitely an easy crockpot meal day! 
.
.
3 chicken breasts
2 Salsa Verde jars
Lettuce
Brown rice
Black beans
Grape tomatoes
Limes
.
.
#dEATS I put 3 chicken breast in my crockpot seasoned with sea salt and pepper. Then poured 2 salsa verde jars on top and cook at low heat for 6-7 hours. Shredded with two forks and it’s ready to go!

#deliciousdish #healthyliving #balancedlifestyle #healthy #healthybowl #bowl #bowls
